          "statistical_significance_assessment_reason": "The confidence interval includes the prespecified >70% threshold and the null hypothesis was not rejected."
        }
      ],
      "secondary_endpoints": [
        "local recurrence",
        "radiation toxicity (grade ≥3, grade 2)",
        "patient‑reported breast satisfaction (Breast‑Q survey)"
      ],
      "study_conclusions": "We demonstrate an effective novel 9 fraction whole breast + lumpectomy boost radiation schedule. This trial uses one of the shortest published radiation schedules for a lumpectomy boost. Although we did not meet our prespecified cosmetic endpoint, no significant cosmetic change from baseline was seen in 80% of patients. We demonstrate excellent local control, and patient-reported satisfaction with low RT-related toxicity. We hope to move this concept forward in a randomized trial against the 5‑day United Kingdom (UK) Fast Forward regimen, inclusive of a simultaneous lumpectomy cavity boost."
    }
